# Git Commit Message Guidelines
#
# <type>(<optional-scope>): <short imperative summary>
#
#
# Types:
# - feat: A new feature
# - fix: A bug fix
# - docs: Documentation only changes
# - style: Changes that do not affect meaning (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc.)
# - refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# - perf: A code change that improves performance
# - test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# - chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries
# - ci: Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): added login with email and password
# fix(api): handled error when no response from server
# docs(readme): added installation steps for Linux users
# style(navbar): adjusted spacing between menu items
# refactor(utils): simplified date parsing logic
# perf(image-uploads): optimized compression before upload; and implemented seo meta tags
# test(profile): added tests for profile update feature
# chore(deps): installed @radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu
# ci(github-actions): added build and deploy workflow
#
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Notes:
# - The first line should not be more than 50 characters.
# - Use past tense: "changed", not "change" or "changes".
# - Be very concise.
